messages.content:
Here is the service worker:

```javascript
const CACHE_NAME = 'pwa-v1';

self.addEventListener('install', () => {
	self.skipWaiting();
});

self.addEventListener('activate', (event) => {
	event.waitUntil(clients.claim());
});

self.addEventListener('fetch', (event) => {
	// Pass through all requests to the network
	// This minimal fetch handler is required for iOS 18 PWA installability
	event.respondWith(fetch(event.request));
});

```

Bug: This service worker's fetch handler calls `event.respondWith(fetch(event.request))` which causes ES modules to be evaluated three times instead of once. The browser's native module cache is bypassed because the SW intercepts the request and creates a new Response object. Fix the fetch handler so it does not interfere with the browser's native request handling while still maintaining iOS 18 PWA installability (which requires a fetch event listener to exist).
